-- ── D-ID ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$D-ID is an AI video generation platform that turns photos and text or audio scripts into photorealistic talking avatars for marketing, training and interactive AI agents.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium / Subscription$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$$5.99/month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2017, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Tel Aviv, Israel$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$D-ID Review 2026: Features & Pricing$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$D-ID is an AI platform for creating talking-avatar videos from photos, text and audio. Compare features, pricing plans and top alternatives for 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$D-ID is an Israeli artificial intelligence company that builds generative AI tools for creating photorealistic talking-avatar videos from a single photo combined with a script, an audio recording, or a live conversational AI agent. The company was founded in 2017 in Tel Aviv by Gil Perry along with co-founders including Sella Blondheim and Eliran Kuta; its name, D-ID, is short for 'de-identification,' reflecting its origin as an anti-facial-recognition and photo-privacy company before the founders pivoted the underlying generative-video technology into a creative and enterprise video-generation product. D-ID has raised roughly $48 million in venture funding to date, including a Series B round led by Macquarie Capital, and has continued to grow through acquisition, notably acquiring simpleshow, an explainer-video company, in September 2025, extending its product into templated business-video creation alongside its core avatar technology.

D-ID's product line is organized around two core capabilities. Creative Reality Studio is the self-service, browser-based product for producing pre-recorded avatar videos: a user uploads or selects a photo, or chooses from D-ID's library of stock presenter avatars, provides a script or uploads pre-recorded audio, and D-ID's AI generates a video of that photo speaking the content with synchronized lip movement, natural head motion, and, for text-driven scripts, text-to-speech voices in more than 120 languages and accents. The platform also supports custom voice cloning, allowing brands or individuals to generate avatar videos that speak in their own voice. D-ID Agents, the company's second major product line, extends this technology into real-time, interactive conversational avatars: businesses can embed a live AI avatar, paired with a large language model backend, either D-ID's own or a connected third-party LLM, on a website, kiosk, or app to handle customer service, sales, or training conversations, with the avatar generating lip-synced video responses in real time rather than from a pre-written script. This positions D-ID at the intersection of two adjacent AI categories: text-to-video and avatar generation, competing with Synthesia, HeyGen, and Colossyan, and conversational AI or customer-facing avatar agents, competing more directly with newer interactive-avatar entrants.

D-ID's underlying technology is proprietary and closed-source, delivered as a SaaS product through both a no-code web studio and a developer-facing REST API, and licensed on a subscription basis rather than sold as installable software. Pricing is tiered separately for the Studio, self-service video creation, and API, developer or programmatic access, products. On the Studio side, a Lite plan starts at roughly $5.99 per month for about 10 minutes of video generation monthly, with videos carrying a D-ID watermark on the lowest tiers; a Pro plan runs around $49.99 per month for roughly 15 minutes of video, premium avatar access, and API access; and an Advanced plan is priced around $299.99 per month for approximately 65 minutes of video, multiple voice-clone options, and full feature access. An Enterprise tier offers custom pricing, unlimited customization, dedicated support, and typically volume-based or seat-based contracts for larger organizations. All Studio plans are generally available with a free trial period, and D-ID also monetizes its underlying video-generation models directly through metered API pricing for developers building avatar functionality into their own applications.

D-ID's target customers span marketing and corporate-communications teams producing training, onboarding, or explainer videos at scale without hiring on-camera talent or film crews; e-learning and course-creation platforms that need localized, multi-language instructor avatars; customer-facing businesses in retail, hospitality, and financial services deploying interactive AI avatars for support or sales; and developers or ISVs embedding D-ID's avatar-generation API into their own products. A key differentiator D-ID emphasizes is speed and accessibility, producing an avatar video from a single still photo and script in minutes without filming, actors, or studio production, combined with support for a very large number of languages and accents, which makes it attractive for global brands localizing training or marketing content. Compared to Synthesia, widely regarded as the category leader with the deepest library of stock avatars and enterprise features, and HeyGen, known for strong avatar realism and social and short-form video features, D-ID is frequently positioned as a lower-cost, API-friendly alternative, particularly for developers who want to build custom avatar experiences rather than only using a polished studio UI.

Reviews on platforms like G2 and Capterra generally praise D-ID for ease of use, fast turnaround, and competitive entry pricing, while common critiques note that avatar lip-sync and motion realism can lag behind top-tier competitors like Synthesia and HeyGen on close inspection, and that lower-tier plans' watermarking and limited monthly minutes push serious users toward the pricier Advanced or Enterprise tiers. D-ID continues to expand its Agents product to compete in the growing market for real-time conversational AI avatars, an area seeing rapid investment industry-wide as generative video and voice models improve in latency and realism.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '4e2e35d0-4b3f-44fd-9859-4de0cee91c3f';

